# Deploy rules

- Option A (Vercel): fast public demo; UI + offline fixture always works; no live Playwright capture.
- Option B (Docker on Render/Railway): adds live URL capture with headless Chromium.
- Bind HTTP servers to `0.0.0.0:$PORT` on Render; filesystem is ephemeral.
- Set `TELL_DISABLE_REPO_SETUP=1` in production — GitHub setup runs arbitrary repo scripts.
- Never commit `.env` or `.env.local`; use hosting dashboard for secrets.
- MCP stays local-only; share web URL for judges, README for Cursor MCP setup.
- If live capture fails in prod, offline `fixtures/reports/tell-report.json` fallback must still load.
